# Integrative Molecular Docking Approaches in Pancreatic Cancer

**Project Title:**  
Integrative Molecular Docking Approaches Targeting Genomic Alterations from Whole Genome & Whole Exome Sequencing in Pancreatic Cancer

**Author:** Afreen Parween  
**Degree:** B.Sc. Biotechnology  
**University:** Jamshedpur Women’s University (2022–2025)  
**Internship:** Digianalix Tech. Institute & Research Solutions, Ranchi (Feb–May 2025)

## Overview
This dissertation project focuses on computational drug discovery for pancreatic cancer.  
- Analyzed genomic alterations using Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS) and Whole Exome Sequencing (WES) data.  
- Performed virtual screening and molecular docking studies.  
- Identified **Luteolin** as a promising lead compound for new drug development.  
- Conducted protein-ligand interaction analysis and network studies.

## Tools & Technologies Used
- **Docking & Visualization:** Chimera, BIOVIA Discovery Studio, Cytoscape  
- **Databases:** BLAST, PDB, GenBank, NCBI  
- **Other:** Python (basics), Data Mining, Pathway Analysis

